1
00:00:33,439 --> 00:00:34,119
Old Chen

2
00:00:34,119 --> 00:00:35,119
Chen Youxi. Old Chen.

3
00:00:35,439 --> 00:00:36,560
Wake up, Old Chen.

4
00:00:39,079 --> 00:00:39,920
Are you okay?

5
00:00:40,399 --> 00:00:41,280
How are you, Old Chen?

6
00:00:41,840 --> 00:00:43,119
I'm fine. What do you mean?

7
00:00:45,159 --> 00:00:45,960
Nothing.

8
00:00:46,159 --> 00:00:47,840
We shouldn't stay here long. Let's go.

9
00:00:59,359 --> 00:01:00,399
Get up. Let's go.

10
00:01:02,159 --> 00:01:03,600
Go, hurry.

11
00:01:46,319 --> 00:01:47,400
Oh my god.

12
00:01:48,040 --> 00:01:49,120
That's a Nightlonging Tree.

13
00:01:49,480 --> 00:01:50,239
What tree?

14
00:01:50,439 --> 00:01:51,719
This is a Triassic plant unique to Guatemala,

15
00:01:51,719 --> 00:01:53,840
Honduras, and Belize.

16
00:01:53,840 --> 00:01:55,359
But it appeared in China.

17
00:01:56,920 --> 00:01:58,359
What's with that tone?

18
00:01:58,879 --> 00:02:00,560
Our People's Republic of China

19
00:02:00,560 --> 00:02:02,359
spans 9.6 million square kilometers.

20
00:02:02,359 --> 00:02:03,599
We have abundant resources.

21
00:02:03,719 --> 00:02:05,400
We have what they have.

22
00:02:05,400 --> 00:02:06,599
What's so strange about it?

23
00:02:08,439 --> 00:02:10,479
Chen Youxi, time for your meds.

24
00:03:07,280 --> 00:03:08,240
Chen Youxi!

25
00:03:08,639 --> 00:03:09,319
Old Chen!

26
00:03:12,080 --> 00:03:12,800
Old Chen!

27
00:03:13,159 --> 00:03:13,719
Chen Youxi!

28
00:03:13,719 --> 00:03:14,560
Old Chen, what's wrong?

29
00:03:14,560 --> 00:03:15,439
What happened?

30
00:03:15,680 --> 00:03:17,159
His heart rate is only 40 to 50.

31
00:03:17,719 --> 00:03:18,360
Look.

32
00:03:18,360 --> 00:03:19,439
Look at his watch.

33
00:03:19,599 --> 00:03:21,599
Why is it spinning like a fan?

34
00:03:23,879 --> 00:03:25,400
Could it be related to the curse?

35
00:03:25,400 --> 00:03:27,199
It must be because he touched that stone.

36
00:03:27,400 --> 00:03:28,680
Let's carry Old Chen

37
00:03:28,680 --> 00:03:30,360
over to that stone.

38
00:03:30,360 --> 00:03:31,560
Let's go, let's go.

39
00:04:30,879 --> 00:04:31,560
Chen Youxi.

40
00:04:32,160 --> 00:04:33,959
Wake up. Wake up.

41
00:04:43,920 --> 00:04:44,720
What's wrong?

42
00:04:45,800 --> 00:04:46,600
Nothing.

43
00:04:52,759 --> 00:04:54,399
Did you think I died just now?

44
00:04:55,319 --> 00:04:56,399
Don't talk nonsense.

45
00:04:56,920 --> 00:04:57,600
Don't worry.

46
00:04:57,879 --> 00:04:59,120
Old Chen is lucky and tough.

47
00:04:59,120 --> 00:05:00,519
I won't die anytime soon.

48
00:05:03,600 --> 00:05:04,639
I'm dizzy too, I'm dizzy too.

49
00:05:05,000 --> 00:05:05,839
Old... Old Lu.

50
00:05:06,000 --> 00:05:07,040
Give me a hug.

51
00:05:07,360 --> 00:05:08,160
Stay away from me.

52
00:05:08,160 --> 00:05:09,079
Hug? Don't gross me out.

53
00:05:09,079 --> 00:05:09,560
Don't go.

54
00:05:09,560 --> 00:05:10,240
Don't go? Stay away from me.

55
00:05:10,240 --> 00:05:10,759
Give me a hug.

56
00:05:11,240 --> 00:05:11,920
Give me a hug.

57
00:05:12,199 --> 00:05:13,279
Hug, hug.

58
00:05:13,839 --> 00:05:15,199
Let's go. Not suitable for children.

59
00:05:15,199 --> 00:05:15,959
Fatty, be gentle.

60
00:05:15,959 --> 00:05:16,680
Gentle, gentle.

61
00:05:17,000 --> 00:05:17,800
It hurts. Be gentle.

62
00:05:18,160 --> 00:05:19,240
How long was I out?

63
00:05:20,680 --> 00:05:21,600
About five minutes.

64
00:05:21,920 --> 00:05:22,720
When did it happen?

65
00:05:23,759 --> 00:05:25,199
You touched this eyeball pattern,

66
00:05:25,199 --> 00:05:26,360
and then you fainted.

67
00:05:26,800 --> 00:05:28,000
Didn't you feel anything?

68
00:05:28,480 --> 00:05:30,079
It felt like a nightmare.

69
00:05:30,800 --> 00:05:31,800
What did you dream about?

70
00:05:33,560 --> 00:05:35,160
I dreamt that I grew old.

71
00:05:35,600 --> 00:05:36,680
With a head full of white hair.

72
00:05:47,959 --> 00:05:48,959
Don't worry.

73
00:05:49,240 --> 00:05:51,199
You still look young and handsome.

74
00:05:51,240 --> 00:05:53,079
But you still need to take your medicine on time.

75
00:05:54,519 --> 00:05:56,000
This stone is really creepy.

76
00:06:03,000 --> 00:06:06,600
Fatty, look how pretty these little flowers are.

77
00:06:07,000 --> 00:06:10,800
It'd be perfect if we could sit and rest for a bit.

78
00:06:12,040 --> 00:06:13,120
Oh my god.

79
00:06:13,759 --> 00:06:14,879
That's a Nightlonging Tree.

80
00:06:15,199 --> 00:06:16,000
What tree?

81
00:06:16,160 --> 00:06:17,360
This is a Triassic plant exclusive to Guatemala,

82
00:06:17,360 --> 00:06:19,480
Honduras, and Belize.

83
00:06:19,560 --> 00:06:21,040
But it appeared in China.

84
00:06:25,959 --> 00:06:27,000
Guatemala,

85
00:06:27,000 --> 00:06:28,120
Honduras...

86
00:06:29,120 --> 00:06:30,959
Aren't those the centers of the Mayan civilization?

87
00:06:31,360 --> 00:06:32,439
Mayan?

88
00:06:33,600 --> 00:06:35,439
That's thousands of miles away from here.

89
00:06:35,639 --> 00:06:37,839
How could the same species be here?

90
00:06:38,160 --> 00:06:41,480
Could it be that the Eurasian and American continents

91
00:06:41,759 --> 00:06:43,480
were really connected in the past?

92
00:06:45,000 --> 00:06:47,680
There are plenty of strange things in this valley.

93
00:06:47,920 --> 00:06:50,560
Just a few lousy flowers and trees,

94
00:06:50,680 --> 00:06:52,040
it's not that mysterious.

95
00:06:52,079 --> 00:06:53,000
Besides,

96
00:06:53,240 --> 00:06:55,160
you say it's exclusive to the Mayan civilization,

97
00:06:55,160 --> 00:06:57,040
and that makes it exclusive?

98
00:06:58,000 --> 00:06:59,519
You biologists

99
00:06:59,519 --> 00:07:01,240
just lack the skills to discover it yourselves,

100
00:07:01,240 --> 00:07:02,480
and insist it doesn't exist elsewhere.

101
00:07:02,639 --> 00:07:03,839
I can't deal with them.

102
00:07:04,519 --> 00:07:05,439
Alright, alright, alright.

103
00:07:09,439 --> 00:07:10,120
Old Chen,

104
00:07:11,199 --> 00:07:12,800
we miscalculated this time.

105
00:07:13,160 --> 00:07:14,800
We should have brought a camcorder.

106
00:07:15,120 --> 00:07:17,040
Look at the mountains and rivers along the way,

107
00:07:17,319 --> 00:07:18,600
the mud pits and ponds.

108
00:07:19,199 --> 00:07:22,240
We could edit it into a scenic documentary.

109
00:07:24,040 --> 00:07:26,560
You haven't mentioned the miasma stingers, wasps,

110
00:07:26,560 --> 00:07:27,959
and the sharp-nosed vipers.

111
00:07:29,000 --> 00:07:30,639
Put those things in there too,

112
00:07:30,759 --> 00:07:32,360
and you can edit an Animal World.

113
00:07:33,399 --> 00:07:35,000
Just filming you two bickering

114
00:07:35,399 --> 00:07:36,920
could make a comedy compilation.

115
00:07:37,600 --> 00:07:39,279
If talking were like traveling,

116
00:07:39,920 --> 00:07:42,040
you two would have met the King of Dian by now.

117
00:07:42,519 --> 00:07:43,360
Old Chen,

118
00:07:43,879 --> 00:07:44,759
let's rest for a bit.

119
00:07:46,079 --> 00:07:46,920
Good lord.

120
00:07:47,879 --> 00:07:49,399
Um, Mr. Lu,

121
00:07:49,680 --> 00:07:51,439
how about we take a picture

122
00:07:51,439 --> 00:07:52,360
as a souvenir?

123
00:07:52,360 --> 00:07:53,120
Sure, sure, sure.

124
00:07:53,120 --> 00:07:54,560
Okay, right here, right here.

125
00:07:55,240 --> 00:07:56,399
Staff Officer He, stand in the middle.

126
00:07:56,399 --> 00:07:57,720
Come, come, come.

127
00:07:59,839 --> 00:08:02,279
One, two, three.

128
00:08:03,600 --> 00:08:04,399
Done.

129
00:08:04,480 --> 00:08:05,839
Let's take a group photo together.

130
00:08:06,399 --> 00:08:07,879
But I didn't bring a tripod.

131
00:08:08,800 --> 00:08:09,600
I have an idea.

132
00:08:13,439 --> 00:08:14,360
Try using this.

133
00:08:14,360 --> 00:08:15,959
How... how does this work?

134
00:08:17,399 --> 00:08:19,120
Turn it around, facing us.

135
00:08:19,199 --> 00:08:19,959
Hold it up.

136
00:08:24,439 --> 00:08:25,759
I... I'll do this.

137
00:08:26,040 --> 00:08:26,680
I...

138
00:08:27,360 --> 00:08:28,079
Come on, get ready.

139
00:08:30,240 --> 00:08:31,720
Ready, done.

140
00:08:33,039 --> 00:08:33,720
Done.

141
00:08:36,200 --> 00:08:37,799
I'm probably not in it, right?

142
00:08:38,840 --> 00:08:39,679
Am... am I in it?

143
00:08:40,159 --> 00:08:40,720
What are you doing?

144
00:08:40,720 --> 00:08:41,559
Let's take another one.

145
00:08:41,559 --> 00:08:41,840
No more photos.

146
00:08:41,840 --> 00:08:42,559
It's quite rare.

147
00:08:42,559 --> 00:08:43,000
No more.

148
00:08:43,039 --> 00:08:43,360
Just one group photo.

149
00:08:43,360 --> 00:08:44,639
No, we can't keep taking photos.

150
00:08:44,639 --> 00:08:45,080
It's not good.

151
00:08:45,080 --> 00:08:46,600
He... He... He Shutong.

152
00:08:47,679 --> 00:08:49,840
Old... Old Chen, let's take one.

153
00:08:50,120 --> 00:08:51,159
It's quite rare.

154
00:08:52,879 --> 00:08:53,320
Buddy,

155
00:08:53,720 --> 00:08:55,279
I might not have been in the last one.

156
00:08:55,720 --> 00:08:57,960
I... I probably wasn't looking.

157
00:08:58,120 --> 00:08:58,840
How about this,

158
00:08:59,000 --> 00:09:00,120
I... I'll take one.

159
00:09:00,120 --> 00:09:00,399
Okay.

160
00:09:00,399 --> 00:09:01,639
Come, give it to me, let me hold it.

161
00:09:03,080 --> 00:09:04,120
Which background?

162
00:09:06,159 --> 00:09:07,519
Mr. Lu, over here.

163
00:09:07,519 --> 00:09:08,120
This background.

164
00:09:08,519 --> 00:09:08,879
Alright.

165
00:09:13,000 --> 00:09:14,480
This thing is interesting.

166
00:09:16,279 --> 00:09:17,240
I'll just stay right here.

167
00:09:22,159 --> 00:09:23,519
Little bug,

168
00:09:24,200 --> 00:09:26,480
you look quite exquisite.

169
00:09:27,240 --> 00:09:28,200
Welcome to the photo.

170
00:09:39,720 --> 00:09:40,440
Be good.

171
00:09:43,919 --> 00:09:44,799
Don't go.

172
00:09:48,519 --> 00:09:49,519
Mr. Lu, don't move.

173
00:09:57,559 --> 00:09:59,039
Wh-What's wrong?

174
00:09:59,159 --> 00:10:00,000
This is a blister beetle.

175
00:10:00,399 --> 00:10:01,360
A blister mastiff?

176
00:10:01,679 --> 00:10:03,960
Even a Tibetan mastiff wouldn't warrant such a fuss.

177
00:10:04,200 --> 00:10:06,159
Order Coleoptera, family Meloidae, genus Mylabris.

178
00:10:06,360 --> 00:10:08,240
The cantharidin secreted from its leg joints...

179
00:10:08,240 --> 00:10:10,440
...will cause redness and blistering upon skin contact.

180
00:10:10,440 --> 00:10:11,000
This blister beetle...

181
00:10:11,000 --> 00:10:13,039
...is one of the most venomous insects in the world.

182
00:10:16,440 --> 00:10:17,080
It's fine.

183
00:10:17,200 --> 00:10:18,759
A n-narrow escape.

184
00:10:18,759 --> 00:10:19,240
It's fine.

185
00:10:19,360 --> 00:10:21,159
Old Lu, did it bite you?

186
00:10:21,159 --> 00:10:22,080
I-I-I... No, no.

187
00:10:22,080 --> 00:10:22,360
No.

188
00:10:22,360 --> 00:10:23,080
No, no.

189
00:10:24,039 --> 00:10:24,799
Alright.

190
00:10:24,799 --> 00:10:25,960
If you're not bitten, let's hurry up and go.

191
00:10:26,039 --> 00:10:27,399
Can't we just walk around it?

192
00:10:27,399 --> 00:10:29,039
Let's go, let's go.

193
00:10:48,000 --> 00:10:49,679
This looks like a shrub patch.

194
00:10:50,080 --> 00:10:52,039
We might have stumbled into their breeding ground.

195
00:10:53,159 --> 00:10:54,200
Then let's hurry up and leave.

196
00:10:54,360 --> 00:10:55,399
Let's not interrupt their breeding.

197
00:10:55,399 --> 00:10:56,080
Right, right, right.

198
00:10:56,919 --> 00:10:57,600
Fatty.

199
00:10:57,799 --> 00:10:58,759
Clear the way with the entrenching tool.

200
00:10:58,919 --> 00:11:00,000
Protect Staff Officer He and cover the rear.

201
00:11:00,120 --> 00:11:00,720
Got it.

202
00:11:03,679 --> 00:11:04,440
Move aside.

203
00:11:18,960 --> 00:11:20,399
Who has sugar? Who has sugar?

204
00:11:20,399 --> 00:11:21,120
I do, I do.

205
00:11:21,120 --> 00:11:21,759
Give it to me.

206
00:11:21,759 --> 00:11:22,440
Here.

207
00:11:22,840 --> 00:11:24,000
This candy is too hard to melt.

208
00:11:24,200 --> 00:11:25,440
Do you have any other sugar?

209
00:11:25,559 --> 00:11:26,600
Will cooking sugar work?

210
00:11:26,600 --> 00:11:27,559
Yes, yes, yes.

211
00:11:29,840 --> 00:11:30,480
Here.

212
00:11:34,159 --> 00:11:34,879
Alcohol.

213
00:11:34,879 --> 00:11:35,519
Alcohol.

214
00:11:35,519 --> 00:11:36,159
Who has alcohol?

215
00:11:36,159 --> 00:11:37,159
I... I have some too.

216
00:11:37,159 --> 00:11:38,039
Here, take it.

217
00:11:44,159 --> 00:11:45,000
What is this?

218
00:11:58,440 --> 00:11:59,159
Is it useful?

219
00:12:00,639 --> 00:12:02,080
Not bad, kid.

220
00:12:02,799 --> 00:12:05,679
It's like the circle the Monkey King drew for Tang Sanzang.

221
00:12:05,679 --> 00:12:07,519
This circle is really something.

222
00:12:08,000 --> 00:12:10,080
But how do we get out of this circle?

223
00:12:12,399 --> 00:12:13,200
I have a way.

224
00:12:13,279 --> 00:12:14,679
Here, sprinkle it here.

225
00:12:15,879 --> 00:12:16,519
Okay.

226
00:12:22,080 --> 00:12:22,720
Done.

227
00:12:23,440 --> 00:12:24,360
It actually works.

228
00:12:25,200 --> 00:12:25,600
Let's go.

229
00:12:25,600 --> 00:12:26,840
Come, walk this way.

230
00:12:28,879 --> 00:12:29,679
Oh my god.

231
00:12:29,799 --> 00:12:30,960
We finally made it down.

232
00:12:32,120 --> 00:12:33,080
They're finally gone.

233
00:12:33,639 --> 00:12:35,440
We finally escaped that mastiff's encirclement.

234
00:12:35,440 --> 00:12:36,200
Scared me to death.

235
00:12:36,200 --> 00:12:36,960
It's not a mastiff.

236
00:12:36,960 --> 00:12:37,919
It's a blister beetle.

237
00:12:38,000 --> 00:12:39,279
Blis... Blister mastiff, blister mastiff.

238
00:12:40,799 --> 00:12:41,919
They're chasing us.

239
00:12:44,159 --> 00:12:45,240
We're out of bug attractant.

240
00:12:45,240 --> 00:12:46,480
No, make more! We're out.

241
00:12:46,480 --> 00:12:47,559
We're out of water.

242
00:12:47,559 --> 00:12:48,200
I have some.

243
00:12:48,200 --> 00:12:49,279
Give me the alcohol and sugar.

244
00:12:49,279 --> 00:12:50,440
Hurry, hurry!

245
00:12:50,639 --> 00:12:51,200
Fatty.

246
00:12:51,200 --> 00:12:52,399
Take them and retreat first, I'll cover the rear.

247
00:12:52,399 --> 00:12:53,000
Hurry!

248
00:12:53,000 --> 00:12:54,120
If we leave, we leave together.

249
00:12:54,120 --> 00:12:55,840
Treat that like a grenade and throw it!

250
00:12:55,840 --> 00:12:56,600
Then we run for our lives!

251
00:12:56,600 --> 00:12:57,759
Stop talking nonsense, retreat!

252
00:12:58,279 --> 00:12:59,039
Hurry up and go!

253
00:13:06,480 --> 00:13:07,240
Hurry up and go!

254
00:13:08,960 --> 00:13:09,639
Hurry up!

255
00:13:14,159 --> 00:13:15,320
Run upwards, hurry!

256
00:13:15,360 --> 00:13:16,080
Go up!

257
00:13:18,759 --> 00:13:19,600
Be careful.

258
00:13:19,679 --> 00:13:20,720
Old Chen, hurry up!

259
00:13:21,120 --> 00:13:21,960
Come up!

260
00:13:22,720 --> 00:13:23,159
Old Chen!

261
00:13:23,159 --> 00:13:24,000
Chen Youxi!
